Preheat your oven to 200°C. Unroll the @puff pastry sheet{1} and lay on a large
#baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{}. Prick the pastry all over with a
#fork{}. Pop onto the top shelf of the oven until lightly golden all over,
~{12-15%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the oven and set to one side.

> TIP: If the middle has risen, gently flatten the pastry with the back of a
> spoon!

Chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm pieces (no need to peel). Pop onto another
large baking tray and sprinkle with half the @dried oregano{1/2}(divided), a
drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on
the middle shelf of the oven until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through cooking.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{2}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).
Quarter the @apple{1} and remove the core and the seeds. Chop into 1cm pieces
(no need to peel). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use
a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}(zested and halved). Heat a
glug of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add
the onion to the pan with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of
@pepper{pinch}. Cook until starting to soften, ~{5%minutes}. Stir regularly.

Once the onion has softened slightly, stir in the apple. Cook until soft and
beginning to colour, ~{5%minutes} more, stirring often, then add the garlic and
the remaining dried oregano. Cook for ~{1%minute} more then remove from the
heat. Stir through half the lemon zest and season to taste with salt and pepper
if necessary.

Use a #spoon{} to spread the onion and apple mixture all over the puff pastry
base, leaving room for a 2-3cm border on all four sides! Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{60%g}(grated) then sprinkle it over the onion mixture in
an even layer. Return to the oven and cook until the cheese has melted and the
pastry is golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

In the meantime, pop the @wild rocket{40%g} into a large #bowl{}. Add a drizzle
of @oil{drizzle}, a squeeze of @lemon{1/2}(juiced) and a pinch of @salt{pinch}
and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat. Once everything is ready, slice the tart into
portions. Share everything between your plates. Dig in!